Written Notice of Intended Disciplinary Meeting

If it is decided that there is a disciplinary case to answer, the Company will write to the employee, giving them a minimum of [insert number] days notice of the meeting and advising the employee of their right to be accompanied to the meeting. At the same time, the Company will provide the employee with written notice informing them that this constitutes the start of the formal disciplinary procedure and as such outline:

the alleged misconduct or poor performance and any possible consequences of these;

the improvement that is required, any timescale for achieving this improvement and any support available (if appropriate);

details as to the time and venue of the disciplinary meeting; and
